Pedigrees are more expensive and chances are comes with more health issues mongrels are generally healthy and cheaper so if you are in doubt go and adopt 😘

Today the family-owned company, headquartered in Albstadt, Germany, is the world's leading supplier of industrial machine needles, precision parts and fine tools, as well as systems and services for the production and joining of textile fabrics. Its products and services support the fields of knitting, weaving, nonwovens, tufting, sewing and spinning.

Hi, I'm Ben Strader.  
For more than 25 years I've spent my career working in the automotive performance and racing industry from grass roots to NASCAR, Off Road Racing to Powerboats, Reno Racing Airplanes to Land Speed Racing record breaking Motorcycles. 

I was  awarded the SEMA 2018 Engine Builder of the Year award for my work on "Project Spinal Tap", an LS7 engine that ran at over 11,200 rpm and I'm also the winningest Crew Chief in NHRA Factory X with 10 National Event wins and the 2024 Championship to my credit. 

Along the way, I've spent thousands of hours as a professional educator, helping others learn the math and science of high performance engines at EFI University, a school I founded in 2003, and now I've created this YouTube channel as a way of sharing more knowledge with you!

If you're interested in how the pro's design, develop and test world class racing and performance engines then be sure to subscribe and stay tuned for TONS of amazing, free info coming your way!

Tras la publicación del disco y una gira nacional en 2024, Chanel inicia una nueva etapa artística con la intención de mostrar su evolución creativa tras un profundo proceso de inmersión en la composición de sus propios temas, así como una renovada propuesta escénica para sus espectáculos de 2025.
En esta nueva fase, Chanel apuesta por una propuesta sonora más potente, con sonidos electrónicos, influencias americanas y una mayor intensidad en sus actuaciones en vivo. Tanto a nivel musical como letrístico, esta etapa refleja a una artista más madura, con dinámicas vocales destacadas y una puesta en escena arrolladora.

description:
Tumble Doctor, LLC conducts world-class tumbling camps, clinics, and classes for cheerleaders, gymnasts, and coaches.
-----------------
There is a huge difference between how gymnasts are trained and how cheerleaders are trained. Gymnasts are trained to perfect every skill prior to progressing to the next skill. Cheerleaders tend to be trained to progress as quickly as possible even if that means skipping (or simply not mastering) fundamental skills. Such training grants gymnasts the ability and confidence to learn new skills the correct way while minimizing fear and injuries. 

Now, we are all humans. We are all subjected to the constraints of gravity, friction, air resistance, tension, etc. These are all constants dictating the way we live and the way we tumble. And thus, only the internal forces are relative; the, proverbial, inner drive is what distinguishes a good athlete from a great one. It is my fervent mission to create confident, technically sound athletes.

description:
From their new millennium rise to MTV superstardom through pop-punk’s modern resurgence, SIMPLE PLAN have been an indelible part of pop culture since forming in Montreal in 1999. They’ve sold 10 million albums worldwide, won multiple Juno Awards, performed at the 2010 Winter Olympics – and, most recently, launched the omnipresent #ImJustAKid TikTok challenge that’s spawned more than 3.4 million videos, including clips from Will Smith, Ed Sheeran, Usher and Venus and Serena Williams.



HARDER THAN IT LOOKS is the first self-released album from dummer Chuck Comeau, vocalist Pierre Bouvier and guitarists Sébastien Lefebvre and Jeff Stinco. The album respects Simple Plan’s storied career while pushing forward in new ways, with songs like “The Antidote,” “Ruin My Life” (ft. Deryck Whibley) and “Congratulations” set to stand as fan favorites for years to come.



“It’s amazingly complex to be in a band for 20-plus years, to keep going, stay relevant and manage all the challenges that come your way,” Bouvier says. “It’s the furthest thing from a ‘simple plan’ – it’s truly a lot harder than it looks. Throughout our career, it’s taken a while to be mature enough to understand that our sound is an asset, not a liability. On this album we said: ‘Let’s just embrace who we are and not be afraid to do what we do best.’ Making a good Simple Plan record is just as hard as making something off the beaten path.

Imagine what the world would look like if you can stretch a 1 second action in 40 seconds.  To do so require specialized cameras that can shoot a minimum of 1000 frames per second.  Yes, 1000 photographs in a single second.    These photographs are stitched together to create super slow motion video.  

To watch such 1 second events in slow motion expands your mind and I assure you - it will relieve stress as well.  So please slow down with me and watch the videos in its fullest.  

While you will see that the natural world dominates the videos, there will be studio shots as well.

Meditation has many incredible benefits for our bodies. It lowers Cortisol (the stress hormone) and Adrenaline while increasing Growth Hormone and Melatonin (the sleep hormone). And all of these chemicals help our bodies function properly, making us happier and more relaxed.

Completion of a Task : When we complete a task, our brain releases a chemical called Dopamine ( pleasure causing chemical ) . Seeing things completed is satisfying. These videos trigger the same brain response as achieving a real-life goal.

description:
Hey, DT here, I've loved golf for 30+ years but haven't played for 20+ years, and am so excited to document my journey getting back on tee.  I'm big on tech and gear, golf technology has come so far, professional-level tech is now available to common golfers like me, data-driven golf is a reality, and it's so cool!

I grew up in the 80s, my high school golf coach custom-fit and made my golf clubs for me in the early 90s using component parts from Golfsmith magazine.  I played a lot of golf growing up.  I worked at a golf course, my high school golf team played a course for free, and friends worked at different golf courses - I literally played golf 7-days a week in high school.  I got to be pretty good, low single-digit handicap, my lowest carded round was 76.  

I stopped playing golf in college, my vision deteriorated (I have an uncorrectable eye disease) to the point I could not see my ball flight.

Yet in 2022, I'm making a comeback to golf!  Thanks for joining me!

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

Rocket science. A term we all use to describe something incredibly difficult. Trying to grasp all of the concepts involved in rocket science can be incredibly intimidating.

Before you knew it, all I wanted to do was learn more and more... the more I learned, the more I wanted to share what was making me so excited. 

But as someone who dropped out of college and has no technical background or degree… I really felt unqualified for the job of explaining rocket science to anyone. But the fact of the matter is, if I can learn this stuff, anyone can. 

Rocket science is awesome, and you don’t need to be a rocket scientist to be excited. 

Everyday Astronaut. Bringing space down to Earth for everyday people.
